-- GE sees Q1 profit up at five of its six units
-- 
-- Fri Jan 18, 2008 8:33am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/01/18/us-ge-outlook-idUSN1829986420080118

 

 BOSTON  (Reuters) - General Electric Co ( GE.N ) said on Friday it expects first-quarter earnings to rise at five of its six units but fall 20 percent at its GE Money consumer-finance arm. 

 The conglomerate expects profit at its largest unit, infrastructure, to rise 15 percent to 20 percent. It sees industrial and NBC Universal profits up 5 percent to 10 percent, with commercial finance and health-care profit up 5 percent, the company said in slides posted to its Web site ahead of a conference call with analysts. Overall, the company expects first-quarter 2008 profit from continuing operations of 50 cents to 53 cents per share. (Reporting by  Scott Malone ; editing by John Wallace)